{
  "texts": [
    "Hassan and White [7] extended support by generating task tours that map out necessary steps for complex tasks, improving users' search efficiency.",
    "[24] presented a proactive approach by predicting and recommending repeated tasks using a novel deep learning framework, pushing towards a future of query-less search engines.",
    "White et al. [30] focused on optimizing task management systems through machine learning models that automatically detect task completion, enhancing digital assistant functionalities.",
    "Furthermore, [14] investigates the dynamic nature of complex search tasks and reveals the nonlinear transitions of task states.",
    "These studies emphasize the importance of task understanding, prediction, and support, thus laying a robust foundation for future innovations in task-based information systems."
  ]
}